>5</b>(3), 237\u2212248.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Bulmer, M., O'Brien, M., Price, S. (2007) \"Troublesome concepts in statistics: a student perspective on what they are and how to learn them\", UniServe Science, Proceedings of the Assessment in Science Teaching and Learning Symposium, University of Sydney, September 28\u221229, 2007, 9 \u2212 15. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://science.uniserve.edu.au/pubs/procs/2007/09.pdf\">PDF</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-12\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">DMUELLER (2015-02-09). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ala.org/acrl/standards/ilframework\">\"Framework for Information Literacy for Higher Education\"</a>. <i>Association of College &amp; Research Libraries (ACRL)</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-10-19</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Association+of+College+%26+Research+Libraries+%28ACRL%29&amp;rft.atitle=Framework+for+Information+Literacy+for+Higher+Education&amp;rft.date=2015-02-09&amp;rft.au=DMUELLER&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ala.org%2Facrl%2Fstandards%2Filframework&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThreshold+knowledge\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-13\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-13\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Rowbottom DP (2007). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1467-9752.2007.00554.x/abstract\">\"Demystifying threshold concepts.\" <i>Journal of Philosophy of Education</i></a>, <